docs.lead_paragraph: The decision of the British and French Governments to extend formal recognition to the regime of General Franco as the actual government of Spain is an important milestone in the civil war in that country. The importance lies in the fact that it puts a definite end to hopes that London and Paris would aid the Loyalist cause. That prospect may now be regarded as definitely buried.

headline.main: RECOGNITION OF FRANCO STRENGTHENS HIS ARM; Formal Action by London and by Paris, Expected Tomorrow, Makes Loyalist Cause Even More Hopeless NEXT MOVE NOW UP TO NEGRIN
